    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-10-22T08:21:30-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-10-22T08:21:30-05:00" n="808"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d808">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_imprecise-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1898-10-22T13:30:30+00:09">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 14.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>In telegram this morning we stated intention to stand strictly on articles of the
                    protocol. We have since read translation of the written memorandum, in which
                    Spaniards make a point that we are unwilling to assume in treaty any
                    responsibility for the protection of life and property during our occupation of
                    Cuba, or to engage to give aid and guidance to Cuba as promised in our note of
                    30th of July. Under the circumstances we deem it important, while refusing to
                    assume Cuban debt, to express readiness to incorporate in treaty properly
                    guarded stipulations, acknowledging and assuming any legal responsibility to
                    which we are by our own declarations and course of conduct committed. We meet
                    Spaniards Monday 2 p.m., and desire instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-10-22T13:30:30+00:09">Sunday, 1.30
                            a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Day.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
